Preheat your #oven{} to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Boil a full #kettle{}, then pour the boiled water into a #saucepan{} with @salt{1/4%tsp} on high heat. Stir in the @macaroni{180%g} and bring back to the boil. Cook until tender, ~{12%minutes}.

Meanwhile, grate the @mature cheddar cheese{90%g}. Halve the @burger buns{2}.

Peel and grate the @garlic clove{1}(peeled and grated) (or use a #garlic press{}).

In a #medium bowl{}, mix together the @balsamic vinegar{12%ml} and @olive oil{1%tbsp} for the dressing. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Halfway through the pasta's cooking time, place the @unconventional plant-based burgers{2} on a lightly oiled large #baking tray{}. Bake on the middle shelf until browned, ~{6-7%minutes}.

Once the pasta is cooked, reserve some of the pasta water into a #colander{} (reserve about @reserved pasta water{50%ml}).

Drain the pasta in a colander and drizzle with oil to keep it from sticking.

Meanwhile, pop the (now empty) saucepan back on medium-high heat with a drizzle of oil. Once hot, add the garlic and fry for ~{1%minute}.

Add the cooked macaroni, @vegetable stock paste{10%g} and reserved pasta water. Bring to the boil, stirring constantly, then remove from the heat.

Vigorously stir the @creme fraiche{150%g} and half the Cheddar into the macaroni until smooth and melted. Taste and season with salt and pepper if needed, then cover with a #lid{} to keep warm.

Once the burgers are cooked, carefully place the remaining cheese on top of them and pop back into the oven until the cheese has melted, ~{2-3%minutes}.

At the same time, pop the buns into the oven to warm through, ~{2-3%minutes}.

When everything's ready, spread the @mayonnaise{2%tbsp} over the bun bases and the @burger sauce{45%g} over the lids. Top the bases with the burgers and some @baby leaf mix{50%g}, then sandwich shut.

Toss the remaining baby leaves in the #bowl{} of dressing.

Serve your craft burgers with the mac & cheese and salad on the side. Enjoy!